  "body": "Parent's values overwrite child's values when I use `--set` syntax, or load values from a values-file. This happens when the child chart has own child chart and exist requirements.yml file.\r\n\r\nHow to catch the bug:\r\n1. Create three charts:\r\n```\r\nhelm create chart1\r\nhelm create chart2\r\nhelm create chart3\r\n```\r\n2. Add requirements to the chart1:\r\n```\r\ncat << EOF > chart1/requirements.yaml\r\ndependencies:\r\n- name: chart2\r\n  version: 0.1.0\r\n  repository: \"file://../chart2\"\r\nEOF\r\n```\r\n3. Add requirements to the chart2:\r\n```\r\ncat << EOF > chart2/requirements.yaml\r\ndependencies:\r\n- name: chart3\r\n  version: 0.1.0\r\n  repository: \"file://../chart3\"\r\nEOF\r\n```\r\n4. Build requirements in charts:\r\n```\r\nhelm dependency build chart2/\r\nhelm dependency build chart1/\r\n```\r\n5. Install:\r\n```\r\nhelm install --dry-run --debug chart1/ --set=image.tag=ERROR | grep ERROR -B 3\r\n```\r\nOutput:\r\n```\r\nCHART: chart1-0.1.0\r\nUSER-SUPPLIED VALUES:\r\nimage:\r\n  tag: ERROR\r\n--\r\n  image:\r\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\r\n    repository: nginx\r\n    tag: ERROR\r\n--\r\nimage:\r\n  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\r\n  repository: nginx\r\n  tag: ERROR\r\n--\r\n    spec:\r\n      containers:\r\n      - name: chart2\r\n        image: \"nginx:ERROR\"\r\n--\r\n    spec:\r\n      containers:\r\n      - name: chart1\r\n        image: \"nginx:ERROR\"\r\n```\r\nHelm version: \r\n```\r\nClient: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.3.1\", GitCommit:\"32562a3040bb5ca690339b9840b6f60f8ce25da4\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\nServer: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.3.1\", GitCommit:\"32562a3040bb5ca690339b9840b6f60f8ce25da4\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n```\r\nRepo with bug: https://github.com/xtimon/helm-bug",
